25/08/2005
ATHENS, Greece - Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis repeated on Wednesday (24 August) that the ruling New Democracy (ND) party is committed to proceeding with reforms. 
Following a meeting of the ND executive council in Athens, Karamanlis said further steps towards implementing necessary structural reforms would be made, regardless of objections in some circles. 
There have been a series of protests in the banking sector and in public administration against draft amendments to social and pension laws. 
(ANA - 24/08/05)
